eNCA's Ayesha Ismail reports. Courtesy of #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - There’s a new sport taking off in Cape Town, and young people in Mitchells Plain are the first to get a taste of it. Drone soccer, first invented in South Korea, is now an official international sport of the World Air Sports Federation. But in order to play, you also need to learn how to build, programme and repair drones. * eNCA's Ayesha Ismail reports.